Ad Text:
At AustralianSuper, we truly care about our colleagues. We know work and life are intertwined. That's why we support the diverse needs of everyone and have policies that enable us all to thrive and be truly flexible. We ensure diversity is celebrated for the opportunity it provides us all to learn and grow and deliver better outcomes for members. We are dedicated to building a high-performance environment underpinned by a strong risk culture, ensuring we deliver the best outcomes for our members.

Make a difference delivering outcomes for our millions of members
Strengthen FICC portfolio oversight across performance, risk, cost and processes
Six-month contract role located in Melbourne or Sydney

Your New Role

The Manager, Portfolio Oversight Fixed Income, Currency & Credit (FICC) is responsible for strengthening and operationalising the FICC Portfolio Oversight Framework. The role provides specialist expertise to build the processes, analytics and capabilities needed for consistent oversight and high quality challenge across performance, risk, cost and investment process. Working with the Senior Manager, FICC Portfolio Oversight, the role will uplift the utilisation of BlackRock's Aladdin analytics by enhancing the data, tooling and workflows that support daily monitoring, reporting and governance activities.

Key responsibilities include:

Enhancing and optimising the use of Aladdin risk and performance analytics within oversight workflows, including data validation, methodology alignment and dashboard specification;
Working in partnership with FICC Capability & Strategy Team to design and embed scalable analytical and data processes that support a unified, whole of FICC oversight view;
Developing robust technical methodologies and templates for core oversight activities, including performance deep dives, risk diagnostics, investment process assessments, liquidity and exposure analysis, and cost analysis, including support for end to end CTC visibility;
Contributing to the design and operationalisation of oversight data structures, analytical workflows, and reporting logic across risk, performance, cost, and exposure domains;
Providing subject matter expertise and direction to support the build of scalable reporting tools, dashboards and automated workflows, ensuring they are set up to deliver clarity, consistency and actionable insight.

What You'll Need

Deep expertise in fixed income & credit management developed over many years practical experience;
Extensive experience in using Aladdin for portfolio management, construction, risk, attribution etc with experience uplifting utilisation of Aladdin analytics workflows;
Experienced interpreting risk and performance reporting;
Skilled in multi‑mandate global portfolio analysis;
Experience building cross‑sector oversight views desirable;
Strong analytical and quantitative problem‑solving capability;
Ability to develop risk governance frameworks;
Skilled at communicating complex insights clearly;
Familiarity with automated reporting and analytical tooling;
Experience improving oversight practices and cost analysis;
Bachelor's or Master's degree in Applied Finance, Data Science, Statistics, or a related field.

This is a six-month contract role located in Melbourne or Sydney.

Life at AustralianSuper

AustralianSuper is committed to colleague development, and we support our people with ongoing learning, coaching and training, as well as career opportunities across our expanding global organisation. We offer generous leave entitlements and promote a blended working environment in which all roles can flex, and we're happy to discuss what this looks like for you.

We cultivate a workplace that champions safety, respect, inclusiveness and diversity. We are committed to supporting our diverse workforce in a way that is inclusive and embraces diversity in all its forms. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process or the role, please let our recruitment team know.

What's Next

Apply now, if you share our values of Energy, Integrity, Generosity of Spirit and Excellent Outcomes and would like the opportunity to work in a challenging, growing and rapidly evolving team to deliver outstanding results.

AustralianSuper uses AI to review resumes and conduct initial phone interviews. This involves processing your resume, cover letter, and voice recording in Australia and the USA to help assess your suitability for the applied role. When invited to an AI phone screening, you may opt for a traditional phone screening instead. For information on how we handle your personal data, please refer to our Candidate Privacy Policy.

https://www.australiansuper.com/careers/candidate-privacy-notice

Australian or New Zealand citizenship or Australian permanent residency status is required.

Agencies please note: this vacancy is being managed directly by AustralianSuper's Talent Acquisition team. We will contact our preferred agency partners should we require additional support. Thank you.
